   <title>Preface</title>
   <section xml:id="preface-purpose">
      <title>Purpose</title>
      <para>This document serves as both the OS Lockdown administrative and user guide. It describes the tasks required
         to install, administer, and run the OS Lockdown application.</para>
   </section>
   <section xml:id="preface-audience">
      <title>Audience</title>
      <para>This guide is intended for system administrators and end users responsible for installing, administering,
         and running the OS Lockdown application.</para>
   </section>
   <section xml:id="preface-conventions">
      <title>Conventions Used in this Guide</title>
      <para>The following conventions identify particular information within the body of this guide.</para>
      <indexterm>
         <primary>Conventions</primary>
      </indexterm>
      <note>
         <para>Notes emphasize additional information.</para>
      </note>
      <warning>
         <para>Warnings alert you to anything that could damage your system, cause loss of data, or expose your system
            to security vulnerabilities.</para>
      </warning>
      <important>
         <para>Alerts you to additional information that must be considered before continuing.</para>
      </important>
      <para>The following typographic conventions are used in this guide:</para>
      <informaltable frame="all">
         <tgroup cols="2">
            <colspec align="left" colwidth="1*"/>
            <colspec align="left" colwidth="1.78*"/>
            <thead>
               <row>
                  <entry align="left">Format</entry>
                  <entry align="left">Description</entry>
               </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <para>Bold font </para>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <para>Used to identify Graphical User Interface (GUI) elements, such as buttons, fields, field
                        labels, and menu items. For example:</para>
                     <para>Type the <emphasis role="bold">IP Address</emphasis> and click <emphasis role="bold"
                           >OK</emphasis>.</para>
                     <para>Select the <emphasis role="bold">Burn Archived Logs to CD</emphasis> checkbox.</para>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <para>Italic font</para>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <para>Used to identify book titles or words that require emphasis. For example:</para>
                     <para>It is <emphasis role="italic">strongly recommended</emphasis> that you read the
                           <emphasis>Userâ€™s Guide</emphasis>.</para>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry>
                     <para>Monospaced font</para>
                  </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <para>Used to identify names of files, directories, and commands. For example:</para>
                     <para>The license file is available here: <filename>/usr/include/sys/license.txt</filename>.</para>
                     <!-- usage: para/filename -->
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry> Monospaced bold font </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <para>When not accompanying screen output, used to identify text that users need to type. For
                        example:</para>
                     <para><userinput>/usr/bin/ls</userinput></para>
                     <!-- usage: /para/userinput/ -->
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry> Shaded monospaced font </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <para>Used to identify screen output. For example:</para>
                     <para>
                        <screen>####### Configuration Information #########
Include "conf/httpd-common.conf"</screen>
                        <!-- usage: /screen -->
                     </para>
                  </entry>
               </row>
               <row>
                  <entry> Shaded monospaced bold font </entry>
                  <entry>
                     <para>When accompanying screen output, used to identify text that users need to type. For
                        example:</para>
                     <para>
                        <screen># <userinput>vi /etc/sysconfig/network</userinput></screen>
                        <!-- usage: /screen/userinput/ -->
                     </para>
                  </entry>
               </row>
            </tbody>
         </tgroup>
      </informaltable>
   </section>
